# nep multi-source configuration
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy these lines into ~/.env (or export them in your shell) to enable
# multiple model sources. nep auto-loads ~/.env at startup.
#
# Each source needs at minimum a BASE_URL. API_KEY and MODEL are optional:
#   - API_KEY defaults to "sk-noop" (local servers ignore it)
#   - MODEL left blank → auto-resolved from the server's /v1/models
#
# API_KEY supports $indirection: $some_key means "look up the env var
# (or ~/.env key) named some_key". Useful when the key already lives
# somewhere and you don't want to duplicate it.

# Comma-separated list of source names. The first is the default at startup.
NEP_SOURCES=local,zai

# --- local: llama.cpp / vLLM on this machine ---------------------------
NEP_SOURCE_LOCAL_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/v1
NEP_SOURCE_LOCAL_API_KEY=sk-noop
# MODEL omitted → auto-resolved from server

# --- zai: Z.ai remote endpoint -----------------------------------------
NEP_SOURCE_ZAI_BASE_URL=https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4
NEP_SOURCE_ZAI_API_KEY=***         # pulls "zai_test" from ~/.env
NEP_SOURCE_ZAI_MODEL=glm-x-preview

# Override the starting source (optional — defaults to the first in NEP_SOURCES)
# export NEP_ACTIVE=zai
